# Release Packaging Policy

Whenever the user asks to "release", "打包发布", "发 release", "cut a version", or similar, **you must build and attach all platform artifacts listed below to the GitHub Release**. Never ship a release with only macOS arm64.

## Required artifacts per release

| Platform | Arch | Artifact name (`<version>` = e.g. `v0.1.1`) | How it's built |
|---|---|---|---|
| macOS | arm64 (Apple Silicon) | `GripLite-<version>-darwin-arm64.dmg` | `wails build -platform darwin/arm64` on macOS |
| macOS | amd64 (Intel) | `GripLite-<version>-darwin-amd64.dmg` | Cross-compile from macOS — works with Wails 2.12 |
| Windows | amd64 | `GripLite-<version>-windows-amd64.zip` (contains `GripLite.exe`) | Cross-compile from macOS — works with Wails 2.12 |
| Linux | amd64 | `GripLite-<version>-linux-amd64.tar.gz` | **⚠️ Wails 2.12 does NOT support cross-compiling to Linux from macOS.** Build via Docker (`wailsapp/wails:*-linux` image) or a Linux host / CI. See "Linux build" section below. |

> If any platform build fails, **do not silently skip it** — surface the error to the user and ask whether to proceed without that platform. For Linux specifically, warn the user up front that it needs a Linux machine / Docker and ask whether to proceed without Linux or pause the release.

## Linux build

Wails 2.12 explicitly warns `Crosscompiling to Linux not currently supported.` when invoked from macOS. Options, in order of preference:

1. **Docker on macOS** — requires Docker Desktop running:
   ```bash
   docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/app -w /app golang:1.24-bookworm bash -c '
     apt-get update && apt-get install -y build-essential pkg-config libgtk-3-dev libwebkit2gtk-4.1-dev nodejs npm &&
     go install github.com/wailsapp/wails/v2/cmd/wails@v2.12.0 &&
     ~/go/bin/wails build -platform linux/amd64 -ldflags "-X main.buildVersion=<version> -X main.buildDate=<date>"
   '
   ```
2. **GitHub Actions** — `ubuntu-latest` runner with the same `wails build` command.
3. **A dedicated Linux host** — SSH in, run `wails build -platform linux/amd64`.

If none of the above is feasible right now, **state this explicitly in the release notes** ("Linux build unavailable for this release — coming in <next version>") rather than pretending it's shipped.

## Build commands

All builds inject version + date via ldflags:

```bash
BUILD_DATE=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)
LDFLAGS="-X main.buildVersion=<version> -X main.buildDate=$BUILD_DATE"
```

Use these exact targets:

```bash
~/go/bin/wails build -clean -platform darwin/arm64   -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
~/go/bin/wails build        -platform darwin/amd64   -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
~/go/bin/wails build        -platform windows/amd64  -ldflags "$LDFLAGS"
# linux/amd64: see "Linux build" section — run via Docker or CI, NOT wails build on macOS.
```

> Only the first call uses `-clean` so the frontend isn't rebuilt four times.

## Packaging

- **macOS** — wrap `build/bin/GripLite.app` in a DMG via `hdiutil create -volname "GripLite <version>" -srcfolder <staging> -ov -format UDZO <file>.dmg`. Include an `Applications` symlink in the staging dir.
- **Windows** — zip `build/bin/GripLite.exe`.
- **Linux** — tar.gz the binary (`tar -czf <file>.tar.gz -C build/bin GripLite`).

Put all artifacts under `dist/` (which is gitignored).

## Release workflow

1. Verify `go test ./...` and `npm run test:e2e` are green.
2. Commit any outstanding changes and push `main`.
3. Tag the release (`git tag -a <version> -m "..."` + `git push origin <version>`).
4. Build all four platforms using the commands above. Cross-compiling from macOS is supported by Wails; `wails doctor` can confirm.
5. Run `./scripts/release.sh <version>` — this is the canonical path; it performs steps 4–6. Only fall back to manual commands if the script is missing.
6. Create the GitHub release with `gh release create <version> --title "GripLite <version>" --notes "..." dist/*.dmg dist/*.zip dist/*.tar.gz`.
7. Verify with `gh release view <version> --json assets` that **all four files** are listed.

## Authentication

`gh` token is stored in macOS Keychain. If `gh auth status` fails, re-authenticate with:

```bash
TOKEN=$(printf "protocol=https\nhost=github.com\n\n" | git credential fill | awk -F= '/^password=/{print $2}')
echo "$TOKEN" | gh auth login --hostname github.com --with-token
```

## Release notes template

Every release's notes must include:
- **Highlights** — what's new / fixed
- **Download table** with one row per artifact + platform
- **macOS note** about unsigned Gatekeeper bypass (`xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine`)
- **Known limitations**

Example:

```markdown
### Download
| Platform | File |
|---|---|
| macOS (Apple Silicon) | `GripLite-v0.1.2-darwin-arm64.dmg` |
| macOS (Intel) | `GripLite-v0.1.2-darwin-amd64.dmg` |
| Windows x64 | `GripLite-v0.1.2-windows-amd64.zip` |
| Linux x64 | `GripLite-v0.1.2-linux-amd64.tar.gz` |
```
